</svg></span>Method<div class="wprm-decoration-line" style="border-color: var(--glacier-header-text);border-width: 2px;"></div><div class="wprm-header-toggle"><a role="button" aria-expanded="false" class="wprm-expandable-button wprm-expandable-button-show" style="color: var(--glacier-header-text)" aria-label="Show Section"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-collapsible-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16"><g class="nc-icon-wrapper" stroke-width="1" fill="none" stroke="var(--glacier-header-text)" stroke-miterlimit="10" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="3.5,9.5 8,5 12.5,9.5 "></polyline></g></svg></span> </a><a role="button" aria-expanded="true" class="wprm-expandable-button wprm-expandable-button-hide" style="color: var(--glacier-header-text)" aria-label="Hide Section"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-collapsible-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16"><g class="nc-icon-wrapper" stroke-width="1" fill="none" stroke="var(--glacier-header-text)" stroke-miterlimit="10" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="3.5,6.5 8,11 12.5,6.5 "></polyline></g></svg></span> </a></div></h3><div class="wprm-internal-container wprm-internal-container-instructions" style="background-color: var(--glacier-background);"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-group"><ol class="wprm-recipe-instructions"><li id="wprm-recipe-18123-step-0-0" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;margin-left: 20px;" value="1"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><span style="display: block;">In a small bowl, combine the paprika, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, and black pepper. Pat the chicken breasts dry with paper towels, then rub the spice mixture evenly over all sides of the chicken.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-18123-step-0-1" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;margin-left: 20px;" value="2"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><span style="display: block;">Heat the olive oil in a large, deep skillet or Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Add the chicken breasts and cook for 5-7 minutes per side, until golden brown and nearly cooked through. Remove the chicken from the skillet and set it aside on a plate.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-18123-step-0-2" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;margin-left: 20px;" value="3"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><span style="display: block;">Add the chopped onion and bell pepper to the same skillet. Cook for 4-5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables have softened.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-18123-step-0-3" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;margin-left: 20px;" value="4"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><span style="display: block;">Stir in the rice and cook for 1 minute, toasting the grains lightly. Pour in the chicken broth, scraping up any browned bits from the bottom of the pan. Bring the mixture to a boil.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-18123-step-0-4" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;margin-left: 20px;" value="5"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><span style="display: block;">Reduce the heat to low, return the chicken breasts to the skillet, and cover. Simmer gently for 18-20 minutes, or until the rice is tender and has absorbed the liquid.</span></div></li><li id="wprm-recipe-18123-step-0-5" class="wprm-recipe-instruction" style="list-style-type: decimal;margin-left: 20px;" value="6"><div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><span style="display: block;">Remove the skillet from the heat. Stir in the sour cream until well combined and the sauce is creamy. Sprinkle with chopped parsley before serving.</span></div></li></ol><div id="ezoic-pub-ad-placeholder-134" data-inserter-version="2" data-placement-location="longer_content"></div><script data-ezoic="1" data-no-optimize="1" data-no-defer="1">ezstandalone.cmd.push(function () { ezstandalone.showAds(134); });</script></div></div></div><div id="recipe-video"></div><div id="recipe-18123-notes" class="wprm-recipe-notes-container wprm-block-text-normal"><h3 class="wprm-recipe-header wprm-recipe-notes-header wprm-block-text-bold wprm-align-left wprm-header-decoration-icon-line wprm-expandable-container-separated wprm-expandable-expanded" style="padding: 10px 20px;background-color: var(--glacier-header-background);"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 28 28" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
<path d="M15.0002 24.5L14.8834 24.3249C14.073 23.1093 13.6678 22.5015 13.1324 22.0614C12.6585 21.6719 12.1124 21.3796 11.5254 21.2014C10.8623 21 10.1318 21 8.67079 21H7.06683C5.76003 21 5.10664 21 4.60752 20.7457C4.16847 20.522 3.81151 20.165 3.58782 19.726C3.3335 19.2269 3.3335 18.5734 3.3335 17.2667V7.23333C3.3335 5.92654 3.3335 5.27315 3.58782 4.77402C3.81151 4.33497 4.16847 3.97802 4.60752 3.75432C5.10664 3.5 5.76003 3.5 7.06683 3.5H7.5335C10.1471 3.5 11.4539 3.5 12.4521 4.00863C13.3302 4.45605 14.0441 5.16995 14.4915 6.04805C15.0002 7.04629 15.0002 8.35309 15.0002 10.9667M15.0002 24.5V10.9667M15.0002 24.5L15.1169 24.3249C15.9273 23.1093 16.3325 22.5015 16.8679 22.0614C17.3418 21.6719 17.8879 21.3796 18.475 21.2014C19.138 21 19.8685 21 21.3296 21H22.9335C24.2403 21 24.8937 21 25.3928 20.7457C25.8318 20.522 26.1888 20.165 26.4125 19.726C26.6668 19.2269 26.6668 18.5734 26.6668 17.2667V7.23333C26.6668 5.92654 26.6668 5.27315 26.4125 4.77402C26.1888 4.33497 25.8318 3.97802 25.3928 3.75432C24.8937 3.5 24.2403 3.5 22.9335 3.5H22.4668C19.8533 3.5 18.5465 3.5 17.5482 4.00863C16.6701 4.45605 15.9562 5.16995 15.5088 6.04805C15.0002 7.04629 15.0002 8.35309 15.0002 10.9667" stroke="var(--glacier-header-text)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
</svg></span>Notes<div class="wprm-decoration-line" style="border-color: var(--glacier-header-text);border-width: 2px;"></div><div class="wprm-header-toggle"><a role="button" aria-expanded="false" class="wprm-expandable-button wprm-expandable-button-show" style="color: var(--glacier-header-text)" aria-label="Show Section"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-collapsible-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16"><g class="nc-icon-wrapper" stroke-width="1" fill="none" stroke="var(--glacier-header-text)" stroke-miterlimit="10" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="3.5,9.5 8,5 12.5,9.5 "></polyline></g></svg></span> </a><a role="button" aria-expanded="true" class="wprm-expandable-button wprm-expandable-button-hide" style="color: var(--glacier-header-text)" aria-label="Hide Section"><span class="wprm-recipe-icon wprm-collapsible-icon"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16"><g class="nc-icon-wrapper" stroke-width="1" fill="none" stroke="var(--glacier-header-text)" stroke-miterlimit="10" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="3.5,6.5 8,11 12.5,6.5 "></polyline></g></svg></span> </a></div></h3><div class="wprm-internal-container wprm-internal-container-notes" style="background-color: var(--glacier-background);"><div class="wprm-recipe-notes"><span style="display: block;">Let sour cream come to room temperature for easier mixing without curdling.</span></div></div></div></div></div></p><div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height:15px" aria-hidden="true"></div><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="nourishing-your-body-with-comfort">Nourishing Your Body with Comfort</h2><p>This <strong>Paprika Chicken Comfort Bowl</strong> isn&#x2019;t just delicious; it&#x2019;s also a wonderfully balanced meal. Chicken breast provides a fantastic source of lean protein, which is essential for muscle repair and keeping you full and satisfied. The dish is a good source of complex carbohydrates from the rice, offering steady energy.</p><p>Paprika is rich in antioxidants like vitamin A and capsaicinoids, which can support overall wellness. By cooking everything in one pan, we also preserve more of the nutrients. For another nutrient-packed meal, my <a href="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/marry-me-chicken-soup/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Marry Me Chicken Soup</a> is a reader favorite. You can learn more about the benefits of a balanced diet from resources like the <a href="https://www.myplate.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">MyPlate guidelines</a>. If you&#8217;re craving more hearty, healthy options, this <a href="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/chicken-stew/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">hearty chicken stew</a> is another fantastic choice.</p><div id="ezoic-pub-ad-placeholder-135" data-inserter-version="2" data-placement-location="longest_content"></div><script data-ezoic="1" data-no-optimize="1" data-no-defer="1">ezstandalone.cmd.push(function () { ezstandalone.showAds(135); });</script><div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height:15px" aria-hidden="true"></div><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="a-lighter-version-for-everyday-enjoyment">A Lighter Version for Everyday Enjoyment</h2><p>If you&#x2019;re looking to lighten up this classic, a few simple swaps work beautifully. You can use Greek yogurt instead of sour cream for a tangy, high-protein creaminess. For a lower-carb option, cauliflower rice is a fantastic substitute that soaks up the sauce wonderfully.</p><p>Simply stir it in during the last 5-7 minutes of cooking. Using a low-sodium chicken broth helps you control the salt content without sacrificing flavor. For inspiration, my <a href="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/hungarian-goulash/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hungarian goulash</a> uses similar spices for a lighter, veggie-packed meal.</p><div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height:15px" aria-hidden="true"></div><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="serving-your-paprika-chicken-comfort-bowl-with-cozy-flair">Serving Your <strong>Paprika Chicken Comfort Bowl</strong> with Cozy Flair</h2><p>I love serving this dish straight from the skillet at the table&#x2014;it feels so rustic and inviting. The aroma alone is enough to gather everyone around. It&#x2019;s a complete meal on its own, but a simple side can make it extra special.</p><div id="ezoic-pub-ad-placeholder-136" data-inserter-version="2" data-placement-location="incontent_5"></div><script data-ezoic="1" data-no-optimize="1" data-no-defer="1">ezstandalone.cmd.push(function () { ezstandalone.showAds(136); });</script><p>A crisp green salad with a light vinaigrette provides a refreshing contrast to the rich, creamy paprika chicken. For a truly cozy night in, pair it with some crusty bread to soak up every last bit of the delicious sauce. This <a href="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/creamy-chicken-soup/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">creamy chicken soup</a> has a similar comforting vibe. A glass of dry white wine or even a sparkling water with lemon completes this easy chicken dinner perfectly. Don&#x2019;t forget to check out this <a href="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/one-pot-lasagna-soup/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">one-pot lasagna soup</a> for another simple, crowd-pleasing idea.</p><img decoding="async" class="gb-media-40763321" src="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/Irresistible-Paprika-Chicken-Comfort-Bowl.webp" alt="Paprika Chicken Comfort Bowl serving presentation" title="Paprika Chicken Comfort Bowl served" /><div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height:15px" aria-hidden="true"></div><div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height:15px" aria-hidden="true"></div><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="common-mistakes-and-how-to-avoid-them">Common Mistakes (And How to Avoid Them)</h2><p>Even the simplest recipes can have pitfalls. Let&#x2019;s make sure your <strong>Paprika Chicken Comfort Bowl</strong> turns out perfectly every time. I&#x2019;ve learned these lessons so you don&#x2019;t have to.</p><p><strong>Why is my chicken dry?</strong> The key is not to overcook it initially. We brown it first, but it finishes cooking gently with the rice. Removing it at the right time ensures juicy, tender chicken every time.</p><div id="ezoic-pub-ad-placeholder-137" data-inserter-version="2" data-placement-location="incontent_6"></div><script data-ezoic="1" data-no-optimize="1" data-no-defer="1">ezstandalone.cmd.push(function () { ezstandalone.showAds(137); });</script><p><strong>Why is my rice gummy?</strong> This usually happens from stirring too much or using the wrong heat. Once you add the broth and bring it to a simmer, reduce the heat to low and keep the lid on. Let the steam do the work. This technique is crucial for dishes like my <a href="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/chicken-pot-pie-soup/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">chicken pot pie soup</a> as well.</p><p><strong>Why did my sour cream curdle?</strong> Always take the skillet off the heat before stirring in the sour cream. Adding it while the dish is too hot can cause it to separate. Letting it come to room temperature first also helps. For more tips on working with dairy, <a href="https://www.healthline.com/nutrition/cooking-with-dairy" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">this guide</a> is helpful. Another great resource for perfecting your technique is my <a href="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/easy-chicken-pho/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">easy chicken pho</a>, which also uses a gentle finishing touch.</p><p>I remember the first time I made a version of this dish years ago, I made nearly all these mistakes. The rice was mushy, and the sauce broke. But that&#x2019;s how we learn! Now, this recipe is my go-to for a guaranteed cozy result.</p><div id="ezoic-pub-ad-placeholder-138" data-inserter-version="2" data-placement-location="incontent_7"></div><script data-ezoic="1" data-no-optimize="1" data-no-defer="1">ezstandalone.cmd.push(function () { ezstandalone.showAds(138); });</script><div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height:15px" aria-hidden="true"></div><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="keeping-the-comfort-going-storage-tips">Keeping the Comfort Going: Storage Tips</h2><p>This dish makes fantastic leftovers, often tasting even better the next day as the flavors meld. I love having a container ready for a quick lunch. Allow the <strong>Paprika Chicken Comfort Bowl</strong> to cool completely before transferring it to an airtight container.</p><p>It will keep in the refrigerator for up to 3 days. To reheat, add a splash of chicken broth or water to a saucepan over low heat, stirring gently until warmed through. The microwave works too, but heat it in short bursts and stir in between to prevent the rice from becoming tough. For another great make-ahead meal, my <a href="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/anti-inflammatory-chicken-soup/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">anti-inflammatory chicken soup</a> stores beautifully. This <a href="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/ginger-chicken-soup/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ginger chicken soup</a> is also a wonderful option for a comforting leftover lunch.</p><div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height:15px" aria-hidden="true"></div><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="why-you-should-try-this-paprika-chicken-comfort-bowl-tonight">Why You Should Try This <strong>Paprika Chicken Comfort Bowl</strong> Tonight</h2><p>This recipe truly represents what I love about cooking: honoring tradition while making it work for today. It&#x2019;s the kind of meal that fills your kitchen with the most incredible smell and your belly with warmth. It&#x2019;s a feel-good classic that never fails to deliver.</p><div id="ezoic-pub-ad-placeholder-139" data-inserter-version="2" data-placement-location="incontent_8"></div><script data-ezoic="1" data-no-optimize="1" data-no-defer="1">ezstandalone.cmd.push(function () { ezstandalone.showAds(139); });</script><p>I promise you, the combination of smoky paprika, tender chicken, and creamy rice is a soul-preserving shortcut on a busy day. It&#x2019;s easier than you think to create a meal that feels this special. For more family-friendly ideas, explore my <a href="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/black-pepper-chicken/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">black pepper chicken</a> or this flavorful <a href="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/moroccan-chicken/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Moroccan chicken</a>. If you&#8217;re looking for a quick, satisfying lunch option, this <a href="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/chicken-avocado-melt/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">chicken avocado melt</a> is always a hit. I hope this <strong>Paprika Chicken Comfort Bowl</strong> becomes a cherished recipe in your home too.</p><div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height:15px" aria-hidden="true"></div><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="more-cozy-chicken-dinners-youll-adore">More Cozy Chicken Dinners You&#8217;ll Adore</h2><p>If you loved the simplicity and warmth of this bowl, you&#8217;ll want to try these other feel-good chicken recipes. They&#8217;re all designed for maximum flavor with minimal fuss.</p>
<a href="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/honey-garlic-chicken-thighs/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Honey Garlic Chicken Thighs</strong></a> &#x2013; Sticky, sweet, and savory thighs that are impossible to resist.<br>
<a href="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/smothered-chicken-and-rice/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Smothered Chicken and Rice</strong></a> &#x2013; The ultimate one-pan comfort food with a rich, gravy-like sauce.<br>
<a href="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/chicken-alfredo-rice-casserole/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Chicken Alfredo Rice Casserole</strong></a> &#x2013; All the creamy indulgence of fettuccine Alfredo in a easy bake.<br>
<a href="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/marry-me-chicken-soup/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Marry Me Chicken Soup</strong></a> &#x2013; A deeply flavorful, romantic soup that&#x2019;s perfect for a cozy night in.<br>
<a href="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/chicken-stew/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Hearty Chicken Stew</strong></a> &#x2013; A chunky, vegetable-packed stew that&#x2019;s a meal in itself.<br>
<a href="https://www.allsavoryrecipes.com/hungarian-goulash/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Hungarian Goulash</strong></a> &#x2013; A paprika-spiced classic that&#x2019;s incredibly comforting and hearty.<div class="wp-block-spacer" style="height:15px" aria-hidden="true"></div><h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently Asked Questions</h2><div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/FAQPage" class="faq-block"><details itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
<summary itemprop="name">Can I use chicken thighs instead of breasts?</summary><div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer"><p itemprop="text">Absolutely. Boneless, skinless chicken thighs work wonderfully in this <strong>Paprika Chicken Comfort Bowl</strong>. They may require a minute or two longer cooking time when browning, as they are often a bit thicker. Their richer flavor pairs beautifully with the smoky paprika.</p><div id="ezoic-pub-ad-placeholder-140" data-inserter-version="2" data-placement-location="incontent_9"></div><script data-ezoic="1" data-no-optimize="1" data-no-defer="1">ezstandalone.cmd.push(function () { ezstandalone.showAds(140); });</script></div>
</details><details itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
<summary itemprop="name">What can I use if I don&#8217;t have sour cream?</summary><div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer"><p itemprop="text">Plain Greek yogurt is the best substitute, providing a similar tangy creaminess. For a dairy-free option, a unsweetened coconut cream or a cashew cream would work well. The goal is to add a creamy element to balance the spices in this comfort bowl dinner.</p></div>
</details><details itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
<summary itemprop="name">Is this paprika chicken recipe gluten-free?</summary><div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer"><p itemprop="text">Yes, this recipe is naturally gluten-free. Just be sure to double-check that your chicken broth is certified gluten-free, as some brands may contain additives with gluten. All the other ingredients, from the paprika to the rice, are naturally safe for a gluten-free diet.</p></div>
</details><details itemscope itemprop="mainEntity" itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
<summary itemprop="name">How can I make this dish spicier?</summary><div itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer"><p itemprop="text">For a kick of heat, use hot paprika instead of sweet or smoked. You could also add a pinch of cayenne pepper to the spice rub or a dash of hot sauce when stirring in the sour cream. Adjust gradually to find your perfect spice level for this healthy paprika chicken.</p><div id="ezoic-pub-ad-placeholder-141" data-inserter-version="2" data-placement-location="incontent_10"></div><script data-ezoic="1" data-no-optimize="1" data-no-defer="1">ezstandalone.cmd.push(function () { ezstandalone.showAds(141); });</script></div>
</details></div></div></div></article></main></div><div class="widget-area sidebar is-right-sidebar" id="right-sidebar"><div class="inside-right-sidebar"><style>@font-face{ 
    font-family: 'Qualion Round';
    src: url('/wp-content/themes/generatepress-child/fonts/qualionround-demibold-webfont.woff2') format('woff2');
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: normal;
    font-display: swap;
 }
:root {
    --primary:       #17497D;
    --primary-light: #DFE9EE;
    --bg-soft:       #FCF6EE;
    --dark:          #565656;
    --font-family:   "Qualion Round", Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
}
.about-me-widget {
    max-width: 400px;
    margin: 20px auto;
    padding: 24px;
    background-color: #fff;
    border-radius: 0;
    box-shadow: none;
    text-align: center;
    font-family: var(--font-family);
    border-top: 2px solid var(--primary-light);
}
.about-me-widget .profile-image {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 350px;
    height: auto;
    object-fit: cover;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    border-radius: 0;
}
.about-me-widget h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-family);
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--dark);
    margin: 15px 0 20px;
}
.about-me-widget .description {
    font-family: var(--font-family);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 25px;
    letter-spacing: 0.3px;
    color: var(--dark);
    opacity: 0.82;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    padding: 0 12px;
}
.about-me-widget .read-more-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-family);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 11px 26px;
    background: #17497D;
    color: #ffffff;
    text-decoration: none;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 0;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease;
    white-space: nowrap;
}
.about-me-widget .read-more-btn:hover {
    background: var(--primary);
    color: #ffffff;
}

/* ===== SOCIAL ICONS ===== */
.about-me-social {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 14px;
    margin-top: 22px;
}
.about-me-social-label {
    font-family: 'Dancing Script', cursive;
    font-size: 20px;
    color: var(--primary);
    margin-right: 4px;
}
.about-me-social a {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    color: var(--dark);
    opacity: 0.6;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease;
}
.about-me-social a:hover { opacity: 1; color: var(--primary); }
.about-me-social svg { width: 16px; height: 16px; fill: currentColor; }

/* ===== DIVIDER ===== */
.about-me-divider {
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--primary-light);
    margin: 24px 0;
}

/* ===== SEARCH ===== */
.about-me-search-title {
    font-family: var(--font-family);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--dark);
    margin: 0 0 14px;
}
.about-me-search-form {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
}
.about-me-search-input {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 11px 44px 11px 14px;
    border: 1px solid var(--primary-light);
    border-radius: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-family);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--dark);
    background: #fff;
    outline: none;
    box-sizing: border-box;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
}
.about-me-search-input:focus { border-color: var(--primary); }
.about-me-search-input::placeholder { color: #bbb; }
.about-me-search-btn {
    position: absolute;
    right: 12px;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    background: transparent;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
}
.about-me-search-btn svg {
    width: 16px;
    height: 16px;
    stroke: var(--primary-light);
    fill: none;
    stroke-width: 2;
    stroke-linecap: round;
    transition: stroke 0.2s ease;
}
.about-me-search-btn:hover svg { stroke: var(--primary); }

/* ===== POPULAR RECIPES ===== */
.about-me-popular-title {
    font-family: var(--font-family);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: 3px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--dark);
    margin: 24px 0 16px;
}
.about-me-popular-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 12px;
}
.about-me-popular-item a {
    text-decoration: none;
    display: block;
}
.about-me-popular-item img {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 2 / 3;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
}
.about-me-popular-item:hover img {
    transform: scale(1.03);
}
.about-me-popular-item-wrap {
    overflow: hidden;
}
.about-me-popular-item-title {
    font-family: var(--font-family);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--dark);
    margin-top: 8px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    text-align: center;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
}
.about-me-popular-item a:hover .about-me-popular-item-title {
    color: var(--primary);
}

/* ===== FOOTER LINE ===== */
.about-me-widget::after {
    content: '';
    display: block;
    margin: 24px auto 0;
    height: 1px;
    width: 60%;
    background: var(--primary-light);
}

@media (max-width: 480px) {
    .about-me-widget { margin: 10px; padding: 20px; max-width: none; }
    .about-me-widget .description { font-size: 12px; padding: 0 8px; }
    .about-me-widget .read-more-btn { font-size: 10px; padding: 10px 20px; }
}</style><div class="about-me-widget">
